# games / phaser

Phaser is a free, open-source (MIT) 2D HTML5 game framework rendering via Canvas and WebGL. This wrapper emits a self-contained `index.html` that loads Phaser from a pinned CDN and boots a single scene drawing a rectangle and title text — a deterministic, committable source you can extend into a full game. For a fixed image, drive the page with a headless browser and snapshot a frame.

controls do
  games.title: { label: "Game title", type: "text" }
  games.cdn: { label: "Phaser CDN pin", type: "text" }
end

## Required reading
- Official Phaser API + docs (MIT, Phaser Studio Inc.) — https://docs.phaser.io/api-documentation/api-documentation
- phaser (game-creator collection, community, opusgamelabs) — https://crossaitools.com/skills/opusgamelabs/game-creator/phaser
- phaser-gamedev (community, pmarashian/cursor-agent-skills) — https://lobehub.com/skills/pmarashian-cursor-agent-skills-phaser-gamedev
- Phaser Game Development (community Claude Code skill, MCP Market) — https://mcpmarket.com/tools/skills/phaser-game-development

## Render
```bash
# The index.html is the deliverable; open it in any browser.
# For a deterministic PNG snapshot of the canvas:
npx playwright install chromium
node -e "const{chromium}=require('playwright');(async()=>{const b=await chromium.launch();const p=await b.newPage();await p.goto('file://'+process.cwd()+'/out/index.html');await p.waitForTimeout(1000);await p.screenshot({path:'out/out.png'});await b.close();})()"
```

## Failure modes
- `type: Phaser.HEADLESS` runs game logic but produces NO pixels — use `Phaser.AUTO`/`Phaser.CANVAS` when an image is the goal.
- The jsdom + node-canvas server path is version-fragile and has no WebGL; prefer real headless Chromium for fidelity.
- Snapshotting before the scene's first tick yields a blank canvas — wait for at least one frame.
- Pin Phaser (`phaser@4.2.1`) and the browser version for reproducible output.
